Martha A. JAMISON and Margaret A. Jamison, Copartners, Doing Business as Jay Street Terminal, Appellee, v. The Steam Tug BOUKER NO. 7, her engines, etc., Bouker Contracting Company, Appellant. No. 378. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 2, 1932. James A. Martin and Foley & Martin, of New York City, for appellant. Courtland Palmer, of Now York City, for appellees.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
